## PART 8 — TECHNICAL RULES & GOTCHAS

### 8.1 JavaScript Reserved Name Conflicts

Never name functions the same as browser globals:
```javascript
// BREAKS: conflicts with window.scrollTo(x, y)
function scrollTo(id) { ... }

// SAFE:
function scrollToSection(id) { ... }
```

### 8.2 No New Tabs for Internal Pages

```javascript
// WRONG:
window.open('page.html', '_blank')

// CORRECT:
window.location = 'page.html'
```

Exception: LinkedIn, email, external URLs can use `window.open`.

### 8.3 Consistent Back Button

```javascript
// ALWAYS use this — never history.back() which fails on direct URL access:
onclick="window.location='index.html'"
```

### 8.4 Career Pathway Scroll-on-Load Bug

Always call `activateEra(0, true)` on init (not `activateEra(0)`) to prevent the page from scrolling to the detail panel on load and hiding the timeline.

### 8.5 SPA goto() Function

For the main portfolio SPA page switching:
```javascript
function goto(pageId, el) {
  document.querySelectorAll('.page').forEach(p => p.classList.remove('active'));
  document.getElementById('page-' + pageId).classList.add('active');
  document.querySelectorAll('.nav-item').forEach(n => n.classList.remove('active'));
  if (el) el.classList.add('active');
  window.scrollTo(0, 0);
}
```

### 8.6 PDF Embedding

```javascript
// In resume-pdf.html — load base64 PDF into iframe:
const byteChars = atob(b64);
const byteArr = new Uint8Array(byteChars.length);
for (let i = 0; i < byteChars.length; i++) byteArr[i] = byteChars.charCodeAt(i);
const blob = new Blob([byteArr], { type: 'application/pdf' });
document.getElementById('pdfFrame').src = URL.createObjectURL(blob);
```

